### Ricoh Fleet Governance API - Examples
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tools

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/
Accept: application/json

###

### Scan Network (Demo Mode)
GET {{baseUrl}}/scan?ip_range=192.168.1.0/24
Accept: application/json

###

### Scan Network (Different Range)
GET {{baseUrl}}/scan?ip_range=10.0.0.0/24
Accept: application/json

###

### Register Printer
POST {{baseUrl}}/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ip": "192.168.1.100",
  "assigned_name": "Impresora Oficina Principal"
}

###

### Register Another Printer
POST {{baseUrl}}/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ip": "192.168.1.101",
  "assigned_name": "Impresora Sala de Reuniones"
}

###

### Get Fleet
GET {{baseUrl}}/fleet
Accept: application/json

###

### Remove Printer from Fleet
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/fleet/192.168.1.100
Accept: application/json

###

### Invalid IP Range (Error Test)
GET {{baseUrl}}/scan?ip_range=invalid
Accept: application/json

###

### Register Non-existent Printer (Error Test)
POST {{baseUrl}}/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ip": "192.168.1.200",
  "assigned_name": "Impresora Inexistente"
}

